Circular Dependency Check Tool (for C/C++)

cdc-tool is a handy program to help you get rid of circular dependencies
between source files in C/C++ code (through #include directive). It
works in batch mode (over command-line) and works under GNU/Linux and MS
Windows.


cdc-tool main directory structure

cdc-tool/
    |-- doc/        -> documentation
    |-- include/    -> header files
    |-- src/        -> source files
    |-- test/       -> source files for tests and sample projects' dirs
    |-- README      -> this README
    `-- SConstruct  -> SCons' config file

